---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Research Philosophy | The Ordinary Computer Scientist"
  description="Principles guiding this research archive."
>
  <article class="stub-page container">
    <p class="label-sm stub-page__eyebrow">Research Philosophy</p>
    <h1>Reading as primary work</h1>
    <p>
      This archive treats careful reading—not rapid consumption—as the central
      activity of technical inquiry. Analyses are written to be revisited, argued
      with, and revised as understanding changes.
    </p>
    <p>
      I am skeptical of interfaces that compress argument into scores, summaries,
      or engagement metrics. If a claim matters, it should survive prose, citation,
      and explicit uncertainty.
    </p>
    <h2>What belongs here</h2>
    <p>
      Paper analyses, systems notes, and engineering reflections where the author
      states assumptions plainly and leaves questions visible. The tone is
      reflective, not promotional.
    </p>
    <h2>What does not</h2>
    <p>
      Product announcements, growth narratives, and content written primarily to
      demonstrate velocity. This site is an archive, not a funnel.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="/papers">Browse the papers archive →</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .stub-page {
    padding: var(--stack-xl) 0;
    max-width: var(--reading-width);
  }

  .stub-page__eyebrow {
    color: var(--color-on-surface-variant);
    margin-bottom: var(--stack-md);
  }

  .stub-page h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-display-lg-mobile);
    margin-bottom: var(--stack-lg);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .stub-page h1 {
      font-size: 2.25rem;
    }
  }

  .stub-page h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-headline-md);
    margin-top: var(--stack-lg);
  }
</style>
